NoExecute — evicts already running pods AND blocks new ones. That is 100% correct! You clearly ran the lab exercise.
Small correction on NoSchedule
You said — "no one can come here only running pod"
That is almost right but one word needs fixing:

NoSchedule = new pods cannot be scheduled here, BUT pods that are already running on the node stay running — they are NOT evicted.

So the difference is:
EffectNew pods blocked?Already running pods evicted?NoScheduleYesNo — they stayNoExecuteYesYes — kicked outPreferNoScheduleTries to avoid, not guaranteedNo
